  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/40035175" />
    <a title="Jill" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1800787-jill"><img alt="Jill" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521336075p2/1800787.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/40035175?book_show_action=true">Dec 13, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jill" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jill" href="/user/show/1800787-jill">Jill</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">anyone who wants their heart strings pulled</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1800787-jill?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer40035175" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5167277830748545371">Capote creates some of the most beautiful sentences I&apos;ve ever read. His characters are created with so much care, and I love them all, whether they&apos;re good or bad. This novella is perhaps the best example of Capote&apos;s skill. Anyone who loves to read gorgeous descriptions of eccentric characters and create a relationship with the story they&apos;re reading should pick up this book. It is the epitome of heart-warming.</span>
  <span id="freeText5167277830748545371" style="display:none">Capote creates some of the most beautiful sentences I've ever read. His characters are created with so much care, and I love them all, whether they're good or bad. This novella is perhaps the best example of Capote's skill. Anyone who loves to read gorgeous descriptions of eccentric characters and create a relationship with the story they're reading should pick up this book. It is the epitome of heart-warming.</span>
