<div id="review_3408028702" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3408028702" />
    <a title="Mia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41744553-mia"><img alt="Mia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1438292375p2/41744553.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3408028702?book_show_action=true">Jun 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mia" href="/user/show/41744553-mia">Mia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9780345803078" href="/book/show/13572998-the-grass-harp-including-a-tree-of-night-and-other-stories">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41744553-mia?shelf=fiction-classics">fiction-classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/41744553-mia?shelf=fiction-stories">fiction-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3408028702" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5223755489262380268">This book offers Truman Capote’s novella <i>The Grass Harp </i> and his <i>A Tree of Night and Other Stories </i>. The novella is an endearing, sentimental homage to friendship and to being true to oneself. But it was the collection of eight short stories which were especially intriguing. Several were deeply disturbing ― if not horrifying ― explorations of fear, alienation, loneliness, our subliminal motivations, and our darker natures. Powerful descriptions, beautiful prose.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


