        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/18951454-the-grass-harp-including-a-tree-of-night-and-other-stories">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12623232-pamela-mclaren?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12623232-pamela-mclaren?shelf=kindle">kindle</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12623232-pamela-mclaren?shelf=literary-fiction">literary-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3093912468" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1984364061817882325">Truman Capote is a strong writer and the first story in this series of short stories starts very sweetly about three endearing misfits — an orphaned boy and two whimsical old ladies—who one day take up residence in a tree house ... but overshadowing everything is sadness for missed opportunities and fractions within the family. It ends sadly and, rather sadly, most of these stories are pretty dark when you get around to it. Not what I expected and not the best for the holidays.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


