        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3214704809" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9541291122933012270">4 1/2 stars. <br/><br/>Teach me to write like Truman Capote. <br/><br/>He writes about the South in such a sleepy, dream like way and his characters are always so interesting - neither sinners nor saints - just complex, flawed human beings.<br/><br/>I loved every story, bar one. Quite a few of them were surprisingly creepy too. <br/><br/>The Grass Harp was beautiful.<br/><br/>This may actually be my favourite Capote I&apos;ve read so far.</span>
  <span id="freeText9541291122933012270" style="display:none">4 1/2 stars. <br /><br />Teach me to write like Truman Capote. <br /><br />He writes about the South in such a sleepy, dream like way and his characters are always so interesting - neither sinners nor saints - just complex, flawed human beings.<br /><br />I loved every story, bar one. Quite a few of them were surprisingly creepy too. <br /><br />The Grass Harp was beautiful.<br /><br />This may actually be my favourite Capote I've read so far.</span>
